7 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to definitions; defining family
resource center; providing for codification; and
9 providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 52 of Title 25, unless there is
15 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 The term "family resource center" means a community, school, or
17 faith-based hub of support services for families that:
18 1. Utilizes an approach that is multigenerational, strengths-
19 based, and family-centered;
20 2. Reflects, and is responsive to, community needs and
21 interests;
22 3. Provides support at no or low cost for participants;
23
24
Req. No. 16340 Page 1

1 4. Builds communities of peer support for families, including
2 kinship families, to develop social connections that reduce
3 isolation and stress; and
4 5. Integrates access to supportive employment services that
5 build skills, strengthen workforce attachment, and promote long-term
6 family stability.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
